HEADWORD: Sopition
<hw>So*pi"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of putting
to sleep, or the state of being put to sleep; sleep.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dementation and <qex>sopition</qex> of reason.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sopor</ent>⟦br⟧
